---
name: scljet-sql-agg-distinct
description: SclJet SQL aggregate DISTINCT — COUNT/SUM/AVG(DISTINCT col), plain and with GROUP BY, matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL aggregate DISTINCT

`COUNT(DISTINCT col)`, `SUM(DISTINCT col)`, `AVG(DISTINCT col)` aggregate over the distinct non-null
values of the argument (nulls ignored, as in sqlite), both over the whole table and per GROUP BY
group. Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file
(verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, dept INTEGER, salary INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlInteger(10L), SqlInteger(100L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(20L), SqlInteger(250L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("cat"), SqlInteger(10L), SqlInteger(300L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(30L), SqlInteger(150L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("eve"), SqlInteger(20L), SqlInteger(250L)),
       List(SqlInteger(6L), SqlText("flo"), SqlInteger(10L), SqlInteger(120L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT dept) FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(dept) FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT SUM(DISTINCT salary) FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT SUM(salary) FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT salary) FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT AVG(DISTINCT dept) FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT dept, COUNT(DISTINCT salary) FROM emp GROUP BY dept")
```
